          <h1 class ="H1">A Tephrochronological Database</h1>
          <p>Tephra layers are proving to be an invaluable tool in palaeoenvironmental 
            studies. The data produced by such research can be difficult to handle 
            and disseminate. <em>Tephrabase</em> is a database of tephra layers 
            found in Iceland, north-west and northern Europe, Russia and central 
            Mexico. D etails on the location, name, age and geochemistry of tephra 
            layers is stored in the database, as well as information about relevent 
            volcanoes and volcanic systems. A comprehensive reference database 
            is also included. </p>
<h1 class ="H1">New version of Tephrabase</h1>


          <p><strong>During 2004 and 2005 Tephrabase has undergone major revision. To 
            use the new version please go to <a
href="http://tsunami.geo.ed.ac.uk/~tephra/">tsunami.geo.ed.ac.uk/~tephra/</a>.  This version 
resides on a new faster server and uses a new version of the Oracle relational database management system. 
All of the computer scripts have been rewritten in PERL, which means that the searches are now more efficient, 
faster with a better formatted output. All geochemical data can be downloaded as a tab delimited file, allowing 
easy importation into spreadsheets such as Excel. Please be aware that changes are still being made and the 
Mexican data in particular is not yet fully available. Over the next few weeks the system will
become fully functional.  The version of Tephrabase you are currently using will continue to run whilst the new system 
is made fully operational [20 April 2005].
</strong></p>
